atches are tested and deployed automatically."},"handling_legacy_systems_and_constraints":{"why":"Legacy systems may not support modern patch delivery mechanisms, requiring alternative strategies.","strategies":[{"approach":"Network segmentation","description":"Isolate legacy systems to limit exposure to vulnerabilities."},{"approach":"Compensating controls","description":"Implement additional security measures to mitigate risks when patches cannot be applied."}],"example_policy":"A policy outlining the use of network segmentation and compensating controls for legacy systems that cannot receive timely patches."},"stakeholder_collaboration_and_governance":{"why":"Effective patch delivery requires collaboration between engineering, security, and management teams.","governance_model":{"name":"RACI matrix","roles":[{"role":"Security Team","responsibility":"Identify vulnerabilities and recommend patches."},{"role":"Engineering Team","responsibility":"Test and deploy patches."},{"role":"Management","responsibility":"Approve patch deployment timelines."}]},"conflict_resolution":"A documented process for resolving conflicts between engineering and security teams regarding patch priorities."},"continuous_improvement_and_updates":{"why":"To incorporate new threat intelligence and lessons learned into the patch delivery policy.","update_process":[{"step":"Monitor CISA alerts","description":"Regularly review alerts from CISA for new ICS vulnerabilities."},{"step":"Review audit findings","description":"Incorporate findings from audits into the patch delivery policy."}],"lessons_learned":"Document lessons learned from incidents and use them to refine the patch delivery policy."}},"standard_compliance":"IEC 62443-4-1","last_updated":"2023-10-25"} 
